Patient: What kind of food should I eat with my heart condition?
Healthcare Educator: Opt for foods low in salt and fat. Eat plenty of fruits, vegetables and lean proteins.

Patient: Can I eat fried chicken?
Healthcare Educator: Fried foods are high in unhealthy fats. It is better to grill or bake your chicken.

Patient: What about canned vegetables? They're cheaper.
Healthcare Educator: Canned vegetables often have added salt. Fresh or frozen vegetables are healthier.

Patient: It's hard to get fresh food in my neighborhood.
Healthcare Educator: Consider local food banks or delivery services for fresher options. Community gardens are also great.

Patient: What about soda and sweets?
Healthcare Educator: Limit them. They're high in sugar which isn't good for your heart. Drink more water instead.